abstract: Karen Crouse On Swimming column discusses American swimmer Michael Phelps, who is busy reading himself for his fifth Olympics.
lead_paragraph: Once a wide-eyed kid and now a waterlogged veteran, Phelps was eager to provide guidance to a young team of Americans, the majority of whom were first-time Olympians.

headline.main: Michael Phelps Heads to Fifth Games Saturated With Wisdom
headline.print_headline: An Olympic Veteran Saturated in Wisdom Joins a Youthful Team
